": "and the latter, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dead person:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb, K:) so accord. to Th, as related by Aboo-'Amr Ez-Záhid: (Msb:) or the former is said by the vulgar to mean the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bier:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, TA:) or the former signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bier with the dead person:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dead person upon the bier:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) and the bier is not so called unless the dead person is upon it: (AAF:) when the dead person is not upon it, it is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sariyrN", "text_ar": "سَرِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naEo$N", "text_ar": "نَعْشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (AAF, S:) but the vulgar say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janaAzapN", "text_ar": "جَنَازَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with fet-h; (S;) which is not allowable: (Lth, As, Mgh, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janaAzapN", "text_ar": "جَنَازَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[so in the TA] signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bier with the man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(En-Nadr, TA:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jnAzp", "text_ar": "جنازة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is derived from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janazahu", "text_ar": "جَنَزَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the first of the senses assigned to it above: (A, Msb, TA:) so some assert: (IDrd, TA:) but ISd says, I know not whether this be correct: (TA:) or a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janaAzap", "text_ar": "جَنَازَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is so called because the clothes are gathered together when the man is upon the bier: ('Abd-Allah Ibn-El-Hasan, TA:) some say that it is Nabathean: (TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janaAy^izu", "text_ar": "جَنَايِزُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) The Arabs say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tarakotuhu jinaAzapF", "text_ar": "تَرَكْتُهُ جِنَازَةً"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I left him a corpse,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dead."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Duriba Alr~ajulu Hat~aY turika janaAzapF", "text_ar": "ضُرِبَ الرَّجُلُ حَتَّى تُرِكَ جَنَازَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[so in the TA,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The man was beaten until he was left a corpse"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (ISh, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rumiYa fiY jinaAzatihi", "text_ar": "رُمِىَ فِى جِنَازَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He died:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he has been carried,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lifted, and put"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "into his bier"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: this they say when they give information of the death of a man: (TA:) and they say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TuEina fiY", "text_ar": "طُعِنَ فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jinaAzatihi", "text_ar": "جِنَازَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning the same. (Lth, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jinaAzapN", "text_ar": "جِنَازَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "janaAzapN", "text_ar": "جَنَازَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A wine-skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when emptied;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though it were a body without a soul]. (K.) A certain impudent man of the Arabs, 'Amr Ibn- Ki'ás, says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wakunotu A_i*aA A^araY ziq~FA SariyEFA\n                      \n                     \n                        yunaAHu EalaY janaAzatihi bakayotu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I used, when I saw a wine-skin laid prostrate, its corpse being wailed over, to weep,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or accord. to Th, as is said in the TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bkY", "text_ar": "بكى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to sing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything oppressive and grievous,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY qawomK", "text_ar": "عَلَى قَوْمٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to a people."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, K.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sick person."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sgh, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["Mgh", "Msb", "K", "As", "IAar", "TA", "S", "AAF", "Lth", "A", "IDrd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}